.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Torrent \- NIP\-35 Torrents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Torrent;
\&
\&    # Create a torrent event (kind 2003)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->to_event(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,
\&        info_hash   => \*(Aqd4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3\*(Aq,
\&        title       => \*(AqExample Torrent\*(Aq,
\&        content     => \*(AqA long description\*(Aq,
\&        files       => [
\&            [\*(Aqvideo.mkv\*(Aq, \*(Aq4294967296\*(Aq],
\&            [\*(Aqsubs.srt\*(Aq, \*(Aq2048\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&        trackers    => [\*(Aqudp://tracker.example.com:6969\*(Aq],
\&        identifiers => [\*(Aqimdb:tt15239678\*(Aq, \*(Aqtmdb:movie:693134\*(Aq],
\&        hashtags    => [\*(Aqmovie\*(Aq, \*(Aq4k\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create a torrent comment (kind 2004)
\&    my $comment = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->comment(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content => \*(AqGreat torrent!\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [[\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $torrent_event_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, \*(Aqroot\*(Aq]],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse a torrent event
\&    my $torrent = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->from_event($event);
\&    say $torrent\->title;       # Example Torrent
\&    say $torrent\->info_hash;   # d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0c1d2e3
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::Torrent\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-35 (Torrents). Kind 2003 events are a simple torrent index
containing enough information to search for content and construct a magnet
link. No torrent files exist on nostr.
.PP
Kind 2004 events are torrent comments that work exactly like kind 1 text
notes and should follow NIP\-10 for tagging.
.SS Tags
.IX Subsection "Tags"
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR \- V1 BitTorrent Info Hash, as seen in the magnet link
\&\f(CW\*(C`magnet:?xt=urn:btih:HASH\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR \- The torrent title
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`file\*(C'\fR \- A file entry including the full path and file size in bytes
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`tracker\*(C'\fR \- (Optional) A tracker URL for this torrent
.SS "Tag prefixes"
.IX Subsection "Tag prefixes"
Tag prefixes (\f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags) label content with external references:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`tcat\*(C'\fR \- Comma\-separated text category path (e.g.
\&\f(CW\*(C`tcat:video,movie,4k\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`newznab\*(C'\fR \- Category ID from newznab
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`tmdb\*(C'\fR \- The Movie Database ID (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`tmdb:movie:693134\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`ttvdb\*(C'\fR \- TV Database ID (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`ttvdb:movie:290272\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`imdb\*(C'\fR \- IMDB ID (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`imdb:tt15239678\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`mal\*(C'\fR \- MyAnimeList ID (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`mal:anime:9253\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`mal:manga:17517\*(C'\fR)
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`anilist\*(C'\fR \- AniList ID
.PP
A second\-level prefix should be included where the database supports
multiple media types.
.PP
To make torrents searchable by general category, you SHOULD include
\&\f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags like \f(CW\*(C`movie\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`tv\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`HD\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`UHD\*(C'\fR, etc.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $torrent = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->new(
\&        info_hash => \*(Aqabc123\*(Aq,
\&        title     => \*(AqExample\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Torrent\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown arguments.
Array fields (\f(CW\*(C`files\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`trackers\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`identifiers\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR) default
to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->to_event(
\&        pubkey      => $hex_pubkey,          # required
\&        info_hash   => $info_hash,           # required (x tag)
\&        title       => $title,               # required (title tag)
\&        content     => $description,         # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        files       => [[$path, $size]],     # optional
\&        trackers    => [$tracker_url],       # optional
\&        identifiers => [$id_string],         # optional (i tags)
\&        hashtags    => [$tag],               # optional (t tags)
\&        created_at  => time(),               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 2003 torrent Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`info_hash\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR are required. The info hash becomes the \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR tag. Files become
\&\f(CW\*(C`file\*(C'\fR tags with path and size. Trackers become \f(CW\*(C`tracker\*(C'\fR tags.
Identifiers become \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags. Hashtags become \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags.
.SS comment
.IX Subsection "comment"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->comment(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content => \*(AqGreat torrent!\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [[\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $torrent_id, \*(Aq\*(Aq, \*(Aqroot\*(Aq]],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 2004 torrent comment Net::Nostr::Event. Works exactly
like a kind 1 event and should follow NIP\-10 for tagging. All arguments
are passed through to "new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $torrent = Net::Nostr::Torrent\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 2003 or 2004 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Torrent\*(C'\fR object.
Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds. For kind 2003, extracts
\&\f(CW\*(C`info_hash\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`files\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`trackers\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`identifiers\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR. For kind 2004, only \f(CW\*(C`description\*(C'\fR
(from content) is populated.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Torrent\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-35 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 2003 or 2004
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 2003 missing \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR tag (info hash)
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 2003 missing \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS info_hash
.IX Subsection "info_hash"
The V1 BitTorrent Info Hash (\f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR tag value).
.SS title
.IX Subsection "title"
The torrent title.
.SS description
.IX Subsection "description"
The long description (event content). Defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS files
.IX Subsection "files"
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a file path and size in bytes.
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS trackers
.IX Subsection "trackers"
Arrayref of tracker URL strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS identifiers
.IX Subsection "identifiers"
Arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tag value strings (tag prefixes like \f(CW\*(C`imdb:tt1234567\*(C'\fR).
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS hashtags
.IX Subsection "hashtags"
Arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tag value strings. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-35 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/35.md>,
Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
